getNameToken

java.lang.String getNameToken()
The name token is the first part of the history token, before the parameters. It is meant to be a unique identifier of a place. An exception will be thrown if two places are registered with the same name token.

Returns:
The name token for this place.

matchesRequest

Parameters:

Returns:
true if the ID matches this place's name.
